# SHL Conversational Assessment Recommender вЂ” Implementation Plan v2

## рџЋЇ Objective
Build a conversational agent that helps hiring managers discover SHL Individual Test Solutions through natural dialogue. The agent clarifies vague queries, recommends 1вЂ“10 assessments with catalog URLs, supports mid-conversation refinement, compares assessments вЂ” all grounded strictly in the provided catalog data.

---

## рџ“Љ Data Summary (What We Have)

### Catalog: `dataset.txt`
- **377 Individual Test Solutions** (pre-scraped, no scraping needed!)
- **Fields per item**: `entity_id`, `name`, `link`, `job_levels`, `languages`, `duration`, `remote`, `adaptive`, `description`, `keys` (test types)
- **Test type distribution**:
  | Key | Count | Letter Code |
  |-----|-------|-------------|
  | Knowledge & Skills | 240 | K |
  | Personality & Behavior | 67 | P |
  | Simulations | 43 | S |
  | Ability & Aptitude | 32 | A |
  | Competencies | 19 | C |
  | Biodata & Situational Judgment | 17 | B |
  | Development & 360 | 7 | D |
  | Assessment Exercises | 2 | E |
- **Job levels**: Director, Entry-Level, Executive, Front Line Manager, General Population, Graduate, Manager, Mid-Professional, Professional Individual Contributor, Supervisor

### Sample Conversations: C1вЂ“C10 (10 traces)
Key patterns observed from reading all 10 conversations:

| ID | Scenario | Turns | Key Behaviors | Final Rec Count |
|----|----------|-------|---------------|----------------|
| C1 | Senior leadership selection | 4 | Clarify в†’ Recommend в†’ Confirm | 3 |
| C2 | Senior Rust engineer | 3 | Handle missing tech в†’ Suggest alternatives + cognitive | 5 |
| C3 | 500 entry-level contact centre | 5 | Clarify language в†’ Recommend в†’ Compare в†’ Confirm | 4 |
| C4 | Graduate financial analysts | 3 | Recommend fast (specific query) в†’ Refine (add SJT) в†’ Confirm | 5 |
| C5 | Sales org re-skilling | 3 | Recommend (development focus) в†’ Compare OPQ vs Sales Report в†’ Confirm | 5 |
| C6 | Plant operators, safety | 3 | Recommend в†’ Compare DSI vs 8.0 в†’ Refine (drop DSI) | 2 |
| C7 | Bilingual healthcare admin | 4 | Handle language constraint в†’ Recommend hybrid в†’ Refuse legal Q в†’ Confirm | 5 |
| C8 | Admin assistants Excel/Word | 3 | Recommend fast в†’ Refine (add simulations) в†’ Confirm | 5 |
| C9 | Senior full-stack engineer (JD) | 7 | Clarify (backend vs full-stack) в†’ Clarify (IC vs lead) в†’ Recommend в†’ Refine (add/drop) в†’ Compare (Java level) в†’ Justify (Verify G+) в†’ Confirm | 7 |
| C10 | Graduate management trainee | 3* | Recommend fast в†’ Pushback on removal в†’ Honor explicit drop | 2 |

### Critical Insights from Conversations

1. **Agent recommends early when query is specific enough** (C4, C5, C6, C8, C10 вЂ” all recommend on turn 1)
2. **Agent clarifies only when genuinely ambiguous** (C1, C3, C9 вЂ” role unclear / language needed / backend vs full-stack)
3. **OPQ32r is a "default personality measure"** вЂ” included proactively in most batteries with explanation
4. **SHL Verify Interactive G+ is the default cognitive test** for senior/graduate roles
5. **Comparisons are grounded** вЂ” differences explained using catalog attributes (C3, C5, C6, C9)
6. **Agent refuses legal/compliance questions** but stays helpful (C7 Turn 3)
7. **Agent pushes back on bad removals** but ultimately honors user's decision (C10 Turn 2-3)
8. **Refinement preserves existing items** вЂ” only adds/removes what's requested (C8, C9)
9. **Final turn always re-emits the full shortlist** with `end_of_conversation: true`
10. **Test type codes in response** use letter codes: K, P, S, A, C, B, D, E (comma-separated for multi-type)

